.SH NAME
Document.getAnimations \- Document: getAnimations() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[CR]getAnimations()\f[R] method of the \f[CR]Document\f[R]
interface returns an array of all \f[CR]Animation\f[R] objects currently
in effect whose target elements are descendants of the document.
This array includes CSS Animations, CSS Transitions, and Web Animations.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
getAnimations()
.EE
.SS Parameters
None.
.SS Return value
An \f[CR]Array\f[R] of \f[CR]Animation\f[R] objects, each representing
one animation currently associated with elements which are descendants
of the \f[CR]Document\f[R] on which it\[cq]s called.
.SH EXAMPLES
The following code snippet will slow down all animations on a page by
halving their \f[CR]Animation.playbackRate\f[R].
.IP
.EX
document.getAnimations().forEach((animation) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  animation.playbackRate *= 0.5;
});
.EE
